 CL regions in the NUHM1. In combination, these new\nconstraints reduce the best-fit values of m_0, m_1/2 in the CMSSM, and increase\nthe global chi^2 from 31.0 to 32.8, reducing the p-value from 12% to 8.5%. In\nthe case of the NUHM1, they have little effect on the best-fit values of m_0,\nm_1/2, but increase the global chi^2 from 28.9 to 31.3, thereby reducing the\np-value from 15% to 9.1%.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 31 Jul 2012 16:50:33 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-05"}
