iometry, the highest transition temperature is obtained when both the\nordered oxygen and lattice defects form fractal patterns, as opposed to\nappearing in isolated spots. We speculate that the relationship between\nmaterial complexity and superconducting transition temperature Tc is actually\nunderpinned by a fundamental relation between Tc and the distribution of\nordered defect networks supported by the materials.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 1 Aug 2012 04:42:17 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 2 Aug 2012 11:50:29 GMT"}],"update_date":"2012-09-28"}
